{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/2018-06-02-side-channel-attacking-browsers-through-css3-features","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"kevinhakanson.com","author":"Kevin Hakanson"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"fcaec303-4892-5ffd-8993-9871f92b97eb","excerpt":"Some people don’t like CSS because it’s not a “real” programing language like JavaScript; other people use CSS to exfiltrate data. Side-channel attacking…","html":"<p>Some people don’t like CSS because it’s not a “real” programing language like JavaScript; other people use CSS to exfiltrate data.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.evonide.com/side-channel-attacking-browsers-through-css3-features/\">Side-channel attacking browsers through CSS3 features | Security Research - Evonide</a></p>\n<blockquote>\n<ul>\n<li>We (co-)discovered a side-channel vulnerability in browser implementations of the CSS3 feature “mix-blend-mode” which allowed to leak visual content from cross-origin iframes.</li>\n<li>We demonstrate the impact of this vulnerability by showing how visiting a malicious site was enough to de-anonymize Facebook users. In particular, exploitation allowed to leak the profile picture, username and likes of unsuspecting visitors all while requiring no additional user interaction.</li>\n<li>This vulnerability affected major browsers like Chrome and Firefox and was disclosed responsibly.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/aa5abb21a8bfe41222e7dbda56d69d9c/fbf08/mix_blend_mode_side_channel.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 50%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Mix Blend Mode Side Channel\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/aa5abb21a8bfe41222e7dbda56d69d9c/fcda8/mix_blend_mode_side_channel.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/aa5abb21a8bfe41222e7dbda56d69d9c/12f09/mix_blend_mode_side_channel.png 148w,\n/static/aa5abb21a8bfe41222e7dbda56d69d9c/e4a3f/mix_blend_mode_side_channel.png 295w,\n/static/aa5abb21a8bfe41222e7dbda56d69d9c/fcda8/mix_blend_mode_side_channel.png 590w,\n/static/aa5abb21a8bfe41222e7dbda56d69d9c/efc66/mix_blend_mode_side_channel.png 885w,\n/static/aa5abb21a8bfe41222e7dbda56d69d9c/fbf08/mix_blend_mode_side_channel.png 962w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n</blockquote>","frontmatter":{"title":"Side-channel attacking browsers through CSS3 features","description":null,"date":"June 2, 2018","tags":["webdev","css","security"],"canonical":null}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/2018-06-02-side-channel-attacking-browsers-through-css3-features","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/2018-05-15-categorizing-backlog-items-using-the-owasp-samm-security-practices"},"frontmatter":{"tags":["security","owasp","agile"]}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/2018-06-22-redis-security-investigation"},"frontmatter":{"tags":["aws","redis","security"]}}}},"staticQueryHashes":["2589769190","97908498"],"slicesMap":{}}